The paper focuses on empirical research in Big Data, which involves analyzing and processing large amounts of data. This aligns with the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases), which deals with the storage, retrieval, and management of data. The paper also discusses the application areas of Big Data, such as cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions the need for empirical methods to strengthen the confidence in reported results, which relates to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the uncharted area of Variety in Big Data, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
